Design (docs):
- Add docs/BOOK-CONTAINER-ARCHITECTURE.md — the concrete North Star data model:
  book = self-contained portable container (templates/ snapshot + data/ outputs),
  pulled from a library (built-in read-only + user-editable overlay, mirroring
  the skills overlay). Decisions: copy-on-create with opt-in re-pull (no
  auto-propagation); whole-workspace host bind-mount; per-artifact schemaVersion
  with a fail-closed compatibility gate (too-old -> quarantine read-only,
  too-new -> read-only; refuse rather than silently coerce; ordered vN->vN+1
  migrations with pre-migration directory backup); and a backup/recovery
  subsystem (default-ON local mirror snapshots, keep-last-N=10 with auto-prune,
  per-book + whole-workspace restore; opt-in cloud zips via layered
  directory-drop -> optional rclone -> optional hook, confirmation-gated at
  setup, never auto-pruned; default content books+library+config, vault and
  runtime state excluded). Documents the collisions, security, migration, and a
  6-phase plan.
